name: SINTREN
description:
Sintren is one of West Java traditional art performances. Sintren master fired up the myrrh as an omen of the beginning of Sintren performance, it was aimed to call spirits that would enter the dancer. Then Sintren dancer was bond and put into
chickenru, and with a very short time her performance had changed. Further mystical meaning was when the dancer imitated audience’s dance with closed eyes, and she would be fainted when other audiences threw coins to her.
